main event: On September 11, 1956, a banana-shaped object was observed in Cartwright, Labrador, moving southeast and slowly rising.
interesting points: The object was described as having a diameter of a pencil and was found to have multicolor features., The sighting lasted for approximately 40 minutes., The observation was made using ground-radar., The source of the observation was military., The conclusion suggested that the sighting was probably an auroral phenomenon.
